Toast @sourdough bread{4%slices}.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @Granny Smith apple{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}.

Spread one side of each bread slice with Dijonnaise. Top half the bread slices, spread sides up, with @Gouda cheese{2%slices}, as much @sliced turkey breast{8%ounce} as you like, and as many apple slices as you like. Top with remaining bread slices, spread sides down. Halve sandwiches on a diagonal.

> TIP: Refrigerate any leftover turkey in an airtight container for up to 1 week.

Divide sandwiches between #plates{}. Serve with any remaining apple slices on the side.